-- Chemicals Release Reported From ExxonMobil Plant in Texas, NRC Reports
-- B y   O l a   G a l a l
-- 2010-10-03T09:01:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-03/release-reported-from-exxonmobil-chemical-texas-plant-nrc-says.html
     Oct. 3 (Bloomberg) --ExxonMobil Chemical Co.â€™s plant in
Beaumont, Texas released benzene, xylene, toluene, ethylene and
nitrogen oxide, according to a filing made to the U.S.  National
Response Center .  The total amount of material released was 3,110 pounds,
which was from a flare stack as part of planned maintenance,
after which the facility shut down, according to the report. The
incident took place at 09:50 a.m. local time on Oct. 1, the
report said.  U.S. refineries must notify the NRC if they release
hazardous substances in excess of reportable quantities,
according to the Comprehensive Environmental Response,
Compensation and Liability Act, known as Superfund.  Bloomberg News could not immediately verify that the
information in the filing was accurate.  To contact the reporter on this story:
